This paper focuses on understanding Chinese parents' awareness and management of their children's online privacy risks, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the study examines the current adoption pattern of digital devices by Chinese families with young children, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the need for better support and guidance for parents, which could be classified under computer and society (cs.CY) and computing and education (cs.CC).
